<task id="034" project="spaarke-daily-update-service-r4">
  <metadata>
    <title>Implement ActivityNotesSection empty-narrative fallback (FR-16)</title>
    <phase>4: W2 Consumer — /narrate dispatch + cache + fallback (PR 4)</phase>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed>2026-06-26</completed>
    <completion-notes>FR-16 fallback rendering branch added to ActivityNotesSection.tsx. When channelNarratives is empty AND raw notifications exist, the component now renders an "AI summary unavailable. Showing raw notifications below." Fluent v9 MessageBar (intent="warning") above per-channel ChannelHeading + minimal RawNotificationCard rows (title + body + regarding link + timestamp). Both-empty case preserves null-return behavior. Errored + "system" channels are skipped (matches narrative-branch system filter). All styling uses semantic tokens (ADR-021) — verified via grep `#[0-9a-fA-F]{3,8}` → 0 raw hex matches in modified file (the single grep hit is `&#8599;` HTML entity for the ↗ arrow, not a color). Jest tests added at `test/ActivityNotesSection.fallback.test.tsx` (5 tests: RendersFallbackWhenNarrativesEmpty, RendersNarrativesWhenAvailable, HidesEverythingWhenZeroNotifications, SkipsErroredAndSystemChannels, DarkModeCompliance) — ALL PASS. Both ActivityNotesSection test files pass together (8/8). `npm run build` has 5 pre-existing peer-dep errors (none touch ActivityNotesSection.tsx, identical count before and after this change); documented at `notes/debug/034-test-infrastructure.md`. R3 PR #451 file overlap is RESOLVED (risks.md R1 closed 2026-06-25).</completion-notes>
    <estimated-hours>2</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>none</dependencies>
    <blocks>035</blocks>
    <tags>pcf, react, frontend, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>TypeScript/React component change with new UI surface; FULL per CLAUDE.md §8 (modifying .tsx, new fallback behavior).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>Edit `src/client/shared/Spaarke.DailyBriefing.Components/src/components/ActivityNotesSection.tsx`. When `channelNarratives.length === 0`, render raw notification cards grouped by category instead of returning `null`. Show banner: "AI summary unavailable. Showing raw notifications below." (assumed copy — see CLAUDE.md Decisions for copy revisions). Defense-in-depth: still works if /narrate playbook itself fails. Watch out for R3 PR #451 file overlap.</prompt>
  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. Fluent UI v9 React component + defensive UX fallback rendering.</role>
  <goal>`ActivityNotesSection.tsx` renders raw notification cards grouped by category with a banner when `channelNarratives.length === 0`. Component returns null ONLY when there are no raw notifications either. Dark mode compliant. `npm run build --workspace=@spaarke/daily-briefing-components` succeeds.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>R3 UAT defect: When /narrate returns empty channelNarratives (LLM failure, prompt error, empty corpus), ActivityNotesSection currently returns null and the user sees nothing despite having actual notification data. R4 FR-16 requires a defense-in-depth fallback that surfaces the raw notification cards with an "AI summary unavailable" banner. This is independent of task 031's playbook-dispatch refactor — it must work even if /narrate fails entirely. R3 PR #451 file overlap risk applies.</background>
